    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="706"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1133 a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    communication dated July 3, 1919 stating that you are in receipt of a telegram
                    from <pb facs="0747" n="635" xml:id="pg_635"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CKEl">Earl Curzon of Kedleston</persName> wherein he
                    states that he has been informed that the American railway troops at Archangel
                    are to be withdrawn about July 15, 1919 and that you have been instructed to
                    bring this matter to the attention of this Department and to urge the United
                    States Government to allow these troops to remain, pointing out that their
                    withdrawal might entail the collapse of the whole Archangel force.</p>
                <p>In reply I beg to inform you that this question is one which was settled by the
                    Supreme War Council and I suggest that it again be taken up with <persName
                        corresp="#p_BGTH1">General Tasker H. Bliss</persName>.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
